        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 5:18PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 517 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
White Deer, or 12 miles east of Panhandle, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pampa, Panhandle, White Deer, Skellytown, and Kingsmill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
